<p><a href="http://lifeandmusic.loricarson.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/IMG_0262.jpg"><img src="http://lifeandmusic.loricarson.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/IMG_0262-224x300.jpg" alt="" title="IMG_0262" width="224" height="300" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-1112" /></a> </p>
<p><a href="http://lifeandmusic.loricarson.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/IMG_0274.jpg"><img src="http://lifeandmusic.loricarson.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/IMG_0274-224x300.jpg" alt="" title="IMG_0274" width="224" height="300" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-1116" /></a></p>
<p>I should be writing but in my defense, I was up before seven this morning, walked Doe on the beach at six-thirty, wrote two pages before nine. Two pages is a good day&#8217;s work for me. Another beautiful day here. It&#8217;s almost too beautiful. This is a dream. I am that woman, sitting with her dog on the beach. The sun glinting on the water. I want to absorb it, take it into me, and back to New York when I go.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
